after two decades of silence?

I found that certainty is the enemy of truth.

The institution wanted me to believe. They wanted me to swallow the mystery and call it bread. But the silence taught me something else: *not knowing* is sacred. The question is holier than the answer. The doubter is closer to God than the one who claims to have found Him.

